# Job Status Tracking & Notifications Implementation Plan

This plan details the technical steps to fulfill the Phase 4 requirements: persistent job status tracking, status filtering, simulated toast notifications, and digest page updates.

## User Review Required

Please review the proposed approach below. The plan strictly adheres to your non-negotiables: no route changes, no existing feature removal, localStorage persistence, and premium design system consistency.

## Proposed Changes

### Global State & Persistence
We will introduce a simple global context for Toast notifications and a robust LocalStorage structure for Job Statuses.

#### [NEW] `src/context/ToastContext.tsx`
- Create a `ToastProvider` that wraps our application.
- Expose an `addToast(message: string)` function.
- Render non-blocking toasts in a fixed container (bottom-right or top-right) with premium styling and auto-dismissal.

#### [NEW] `src/hooks/useJobStatus.ts`
- Create a custom React hook to manage reading and writing from `localStorage` under the key `jobTrackerStatus`.
- The data structure will be: `Record<string, { status: string, date: string }>` mapping `jobId` to a status object.
- Provide a `updateJobStatus(jobId, newStatus)` function that triggers the contextual Toast on change.

---

### Components

#### [MODIFY] [src/App.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/App.tsx)
- Wrap the main application tree with the `ToastProvider` so notifications can be triggered from any route.

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/Job/JobCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/components/Job/JobCard.tsx)
- Add an interactive Status Button Group or Dropdown to select: "Not Applied", "Applied", "Rejected", "Selected".
- Apply dynamic badge colors per the spec:
  - Not Applied → neutral (grey)
  - Applied → blue (`#2563EB` or similar muted premium blue)
  - Rejected → red (`--color-accent` / deep red)
  - Selected → green (`--color-success` / muted green)

#### [MODIFY] [src/components/Job/FilterBar.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/components/Job/FilterBar.tsx)
- Append a new `status` field to [FilterState](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/components/Job/FilterBar.tsx#3-12) ("All", "Not Applied", "Applied", "Rejected", "Selected").
- Add the corresponding select element to the FilterBar UI.

---

### Pages

#### [MODIFY] [src/pages/Dashboard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/pages/Dashboard.tsx)
- Integrate `useJobStatus` hook.
- Update the job mapping to pass the current status to the [JobCard](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/components/Job/JobCard.tsx#26-108).
- Update the filtering engine (AND logic) to check the target job's status against the [FilterState](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/components/Job/FilterBar.tsx#3-12). If no status exists in `localStorage`, it defaults to "Not Applied".

#### [MODIFY] [src/pages/Saved.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/pages/Saved.tsx)
- Integrate `useJobStatus` hook to render statuses properly on saved jobs.

#### [MODIFY] [src/pages/Digest.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sanja/Downloads/Kodnest_Projects/Job%20Notification%20Tracker/src/pages/Digest.tsx)
- Parse `jobTrackerStatus` from `localStorage` on load.
- Filter out "Not Applied" to compile a list of active applications.
- Build a new UI section under the email digest: "Recent Status Updates".
- Match IDs with `jobsData` to display Title, Company, Status, and Date Changed.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1. Navigate to `/dashboard` and view any Job Card. It should default to "Not Applied".
2. Change the status of Job A to "Applied". A sleek Toast notification reading "Status updated: Applied" should appear and auto-dismiss.
3. Refresh the page. Job A should still display "Applied" rendered in blue.
4. Open the Filter Bar and select "Applied". The list should instantly filter down to show only Job A. Add a Keyword filter to ensure the AND logic still functions perfectly.
5. Navigate to `/digest`. You should see Job A listed in the "Recent Status Updates" block at the bottom, alongside the current date.
6. Clear LocalStorage and refresh. Confirm that no crashes occur and everything reverts safely to "Not Applied".
